| quote = The term ["animism"] clearly began as an expression of a nest of insulting approaches to indigenous peoples and the earliest putatively religious humans. It was, and sometimes remains, a colonialist slur.
| source = —Graham Harvey, 2005.{{sfn|Harvey|2005|p=xiii}}
| align = left
| width = 25em
